title: Eliades Ochoa with Manu Dibango - CubAfrica (1999)

The result is an authentic and very passionate Cuban son that spills out with the freshness of a bubbly Cameroonian Makossa sound. 
Listen to Dibango's vintage saxophone take full flight on the track "Rumba Makossa" while Ochoa leads the pack on one of the best rumba ever.

Every note, every nuance emanates with a vibrant sense of fun, a lot of fun. 
And the guys seem to truly enjoy themselves.
